PrecisAmendment to the CANADIAN INTERNATIONAL TRADE TRIBUNAL REGULATIONS which authorizes the Chairman to determine that, under specific circumstances, one member of the Tribunal constitutes a quorum thereof, thereby providing the Tribunal with enough flexibility to manage the expected increase in its workload resulting from the implementation of the World Trade Organization Agreement.

precis:
Amendment to the CANADIAN INTERNATIONAL TRADE TRIBUNAL REGULATIONS which
authorizes the Chairman to determine that, under specific circumstances,
one member of the Tribunal constitutes a quorum thereof, thereby
providing the Tribunal with enough flexibility to manage the expected
increase in its workload resulting from the implementation of the World
Trade Organization Agreement.
